

## Setup In Ubuntu


To Manage PHP Dependency Libraries and Modules, 
Laravel Use *Composer*. To Make Your Process Easy, here I am providing you a 
simple few series of commands to quickly setup laravel in your Ubuntu..
 
- `sudo apt-get update`
- `sudo apt-get install composer`
- `sudo apt-get install php7.3-*`
- `sudo apt-get install apache2 libapache2-mod-php7.3 mysql-server php7.3 php7.3-xml php7.3-gd php7.3-opcache php7.3-mbstring php7.3-mysql`
- `composer global require laravel/installer`
- `git clone https://github.com/blaregroup/UniversityPortal`
- `cd UniversityPortal`
- `echo "export PATH=$PATH:~/.config/composer/vendor/bin" >> ~/.bashrc`

Start new Terminal And Now Laravel Setup is Ready To Go



